Study 3: Canada & US Dimensionality Robustness Check
======================================================
Copy and paste the text below into your manuscript:

--- Canada ---
For Canada, EGA suggested an exploratory 3-dimension structure. A chi-square difference test showed this 3-factor model fit significantly better than the theoretical 2-factor model (Δχ²(2) = 340.4, p < .001). While the exploratory 3-factor structure yielded a statistical improvement in chi-square due to the estimation of additional parameters, the theory-driven 2-factor model maintained an adequate overall fit without artificially fragmenting the constructs. Therefore, we retained the theoretical 2-factor structure for cross-cultural consistency.

--- United States ---
For United States, EGA suggested an exploratory 3-dimension structure. However, a formal Confirmatory Factor Analysis (CFA) of this 3-factor structure failed to converge, indicating that the empirically derived dimensions were mathematically unstable. In contrast, the theory-driven 2-factor model converged successfully and demonstrated adequate fit. Therefore, we retained the 2-factor structure.

